# Trial INDEX

List of numbered research notebooks / trials. `scripts/new_purpose.py` adds
new entries automatically.

## Entries

| trial_id | mode | linked hypothesis | state row updated | notebook status | state update / result summary |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|

## Notebook-status legend (per notebook)

- `planned`: accepted through the entry gate, notebook not created
- `in-progress`: notebook created, trial not yet interpreted
- `done`: observation, interpretation, and research-state update are recorded
- `parked`: blocked on upstream dependency
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing; reason recorded in decisions.md

A notebook is `done` only when it changes the project state. A metric without
an update to `research_state.md`, `hypotheses.md`, or `decisions.md` is still
unfinished.

## Order

Sequential numbering is for auditability. Dependencies and blocking state rows
take precedence over chronology when deciding what to run next.
